      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests demonstrating expected convergence rates for momentum and scalar transport equations relevant to hemolysis index computation.",
      "rationale": "Method-of-manufactured-solutions verification performed for momentum equations demonstrating second-order convergence. Scalar transport (hemolysis power-law source term) verification incomplete; formal order-of-accuracy test not executed for the released build."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for hemolysis index QoI across all operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "GCI study performed on three systematically refined meshes (2.1M, 6.8M, 18.4M cells). GCI for velocity fields is 3.2%; GCI for hemolysis index reaches 7.1% at the highest flow rate operating point, exceeding the 5% threshold. Mesh refinement study was executed under the rc2 build; results assumed transferable to the released build without re-execution."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid properties, rotational speed, flow rates) match COU operating envelope within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments conducted with blood analog fluid (glycerin-water) at 23°C; COU involves whole blood at 37°C. Viscosity correction applied via Newtonian approximation. Non-Newtonian effects at low shear rates not characterized in experimental dataset, introducing condition mismatch at MRL 5 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., normalized RMS error or area validation metric) computed with uncertainty propagation for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Normalized RMS error computed for velocity fields (8.3%) and NIH (18%). Area validation metric not computed; comparison is point-wise rather than distributional. Uncertainty in experimental NIH measurements not fully propagated into the comparison metric, limiting rigor of output comparison at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs (velocity fields, NIH) are directly mapped to COU decision QoIs with documented traceability.",
      "rationale": "Velocity field QoI is an intermediate quantity; the primary COU QoI is absolute NIH below clinical threshold. Traceability from velocity validation to hemolysis prediction is established through the power-law hemolysis model, but sensitivity of NIH to velocity field errors is not formally quantified, weakening the relevance argument at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed under geometry, boundary conditions, and operating conditions representative of the COU VAD device.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is not the specific VAD device geometry. Geometric similarity is assumed but not demonstrated. Operating conditions span 3 of 5 COU flow-speed combinations; 2 operating points extrapolate beyond the validated envelope."
    },
