      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of turbulence model selection (SST k-omega) and hemolysis power-law model form with sensitivity analysis demonstrating low sensitivity to model form choices.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on prior literature for rotating machinery; no formal model form sensitivity study comparing alternative turbulence closures (e.g., RSM, LES) performed. Power-law hemolysis model coefficients sourced from Giersiepen et al. (1990); model form uncertainty not quantified. Model form credibility is the most significant gap at MRL 5."
    },
